The API-Server can be configured via a config file (YAML, JSON or TOML) located at /etc/enclave/config.yaml, $HOME/.enclave or ./. The configuration file supports the following options: Option Allowed Values Description human_readable_output true / false Enable Human-reable output (= to stdout and in color) for the logs log_level debug, info, warn or error Set the log-level production_environment true / false Operate (gin) server in production mode port <port> Port to run the API-Server on

POST /rbac/endpoint Assign an endpoint to a specific resource group.

Responses‚Äã 201 400 401 403 404 413 500 Endpoint assigned to resource group successfully or was already assigned. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. The request payload is too large. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
POST /rbac/user Assign role to a specific user.

Responses‚Äã 201 400 401 403 404 413 500 Role assigned to user successfully or role was already assigned. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. The requested resource was not found. The request payload is too large. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
HEAD /artifact Check if a specific artifact exists based on its fully qualified name (FQN).
Responses‚Äã 200 400 401 403 404 413 500 Artifact exists. Bad request. Unauthorized. Forbidden. Artifact does not exist. The request payload is too large. Internal server error.
HEAD /rbac/resource-group Check if a specific resource group exists in the system.
Responses‚Äã 200 400 401 403 404 413 500 Resource group exists. Bad request. Unauthorized. Forbidden. Resource group does not exist. The request payload is too large. Internal server error.
HEAD /rbac/role Check if a specific role exists in the system.
Responses‚Äã 200 400 401 403 404 413 500 Role exists. Bad request. Unauthorized. Forbidden. Role does not exist. The request payload is too large. Internal server error.
HEAD /users/user Check if a specific user exists.
Responses‚Äã 200 400 401 403 404 413 500 User exists. Bad request. Unauthorized. Forbidden. User does not exist. The request payload is too large. Internal server error.
POST /manifest Create a new manifest from YAML manifest data.

Responses‚Äã 201 400 401 403 409 500 Manifest created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. A manifest with the given name already exists. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
POST /rbac/policy Create a new role-based access control (RBAC) policy.

Responses‚Äã 201 400 401 403 404 413 500 RBAC policy created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. One or more fields were invalid. The request payload is too large. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
POST /rbac/resource-group Create a new resource group.

Responses‚Äã 201 400 401 403 409 413 500 Resource group created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. Resource group already exists. The request payload is too large. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.

Responses‚Äã 201 400 401 403 409 413 500 Role created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. Responses‚Äã 201 400 401 403 409 413 500 User created successfully. The request was malformed or invalid. The provided authentication credentials were invalid. The authenticated user does not have permission to access the requested resource. User already exists. The request payload is too large. An internal server error occurred. Look at the server logs for more details.
